    <name>The Four Corners Activity:​ Learning Variability-in-Context​</name>
    <intro></intro>
    <introformat>1</introformat>
    <content>&lt;div class="editor-indent" style="margin-left: 30px;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/icon-compass-purple.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_right"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;p&gt;The
goal of the &lt;strong&gt;four corners activity&lt;/strong&gt; is for&amp;nbsp;learners to show their position on a specific
statement by standing in a particular corner of the room. This activity elicits
the participation of all learners by requiring everyone to take a position. Use
this as a warm-up activity by asking students to respond to the statements
provided and then indicate if they identify as either North, South, East, or
West in the situation described.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ultimately, you may want to use this activity to
demonstrate that learning is contextual. &lt;strong&gt;How someone learns or engages with an
activity will vary depending on the context of the experience.&lt;/strong&gt; This is true for
all learners and is an important concept to keep in mind both as an educator
and when you are trying to learn something new.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;To include the four corners activity in your classroom, follow these steps:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prepare the room: &lt;/strong&gt;Label
the four corners of the room with signs reading “North,"
"South," "East," and "West."&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prepare the learners:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Describe
the learning characteristics of each of the directions:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;North:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Likes to&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;take action&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;, try things, and&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;plunge in.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;East:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Likes to look at the&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;big picture&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;and the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;possibilities before acting.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;South:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Likes to consider&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;everyone's feelings&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;hear&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;all voices&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;before acting.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;West:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Likes to know the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;who, what, when, where,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;how,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;and why before acting.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;After
this initial reading, ask learners to go to the corner of the room they resonate
most strongly with.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Engage in the activity:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt; Read
each of the statements (one at a time) provided below.&amp;nbsp; After reading each statement ask learners if they
are a North, South, East or West. Consider asking: Would you change your
"go to" approach based on the situation? Are you still a North? Do
you think your approach would be different in this situation? How? Why?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;p&gt;Here are three example statements you might want to read while doing the four corners activity.&amp;nbsp; As you read them, try to think of other statements you might want to use for your class.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/compass%20%281%29.jpg" alt="An artistic sketch of a compass with the N, W, S, and E labeled." width="50" height="40"&gt;North:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Plunge in |&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Look at the big picture |&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Consider feelings |&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;West:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Pay attention to detail&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/grocery.jpg" alt="A produce stand with baskets of pears, apples, oranges, cucumbers, and tomatoes placed on a brown wooden table." width="100" height="66" class="atto_image_button_middle"&gt;&lt;strong style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;S&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;cenario 1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;​:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.7rem; font-weight: 400;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem; font-weight: 400;"&gt;You are&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem; font-weight: 400;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;grocery shopping&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem; font-weight: 400;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;in&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem; font-weight: 400;"&gt;a market&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem; font-weight: 400;"&gt;you know well&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem; font-weight: 400;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/cake%20and%20ballons.jpg" alt="A white table containing a strawberry and whip cream cake with yellow, blue, and red balloons and other sparkly decorations." width="100" height="66" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_middle"&gt;Scenario 2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;​:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;You are&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;planning a party&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;for&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;your&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;best friend’s&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;birthday.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/committee.jpg" alt="Three people working at a table with a notebooks, pens, and coffee in a dark room, contrasted by a bright window behind them." width="100" height="69" class="atto_image_button_middle"&gt;&lt;strong style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Scenario 3:&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;​&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;You are&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;on a committee&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;that&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;is deciding which
curriculum&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;to purchase.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;​Go back to the&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="$@COURSEVIEWBYID*291@$#section-5" target="_blank"&gt;Try It Yourself Section&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;for a list of all Try it Yourself Options.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/divider-wave-1.png" alt="" width="1920" height="195" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_text-bottom"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
